\f0\b\fs34 \cf2 1. Purpose of this Privacy Policy
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Memorial Flight Co Pty Ltd ACN trading as Memorial Flight Co Pty Ltd, together with our officers, employees, contractors, agents, and authorised service providers, referred to in this Privacy Policy as 
\f2\b Memorial Flight Co
\f1\b0 , 
\f2\b we
\f1\b0 , 
\f2\b us
\f1\b0 , or 
\f2\b our
\f1\b0 , is committed to protecting privacy and handling personal information respectfully, lawfully, and securely.\
\
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, hold, use, disclose, store, and otherwise handle personal information in connection with our website, enquiries, bookings, memorial flight services, ash-scattering services, media deliverables, customer communications, and related business activities.\
\
By using our website, contacting us, submitting information to us, placing a booking, making payment, sending cremated remains to us, or otherwise engaging with us, you acknowledge that your personal information will be handled in accordance with this Privacy Policy.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 2. What this Privacy Policy covers
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
This Privacy Policy applies to personal information collected by us through:\
\
a. our website and any associated forms, payment pages, portals, booking systems, and digital channels;\
\
b. email, telephone, SMS, messaging platforms, and postal correspondence;\
\
c. quotes, enquiries, service bookings, intake forms, delivery forms, and declarations;\
\
d. payment, invoicing, and administration processes;\
\
e. customer service interactions;\
\
f. service records, memorial records, and media delivery processes; and\
\
g. our dealings with funeral providers, cremation providers, couriers, contractors, service partners, and other authorised representatives.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 3. Definitions
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
In this Privacy Policy, unless the context otherwise requires:\
\
