\f0\b\fs34 \cf2 5. Sensitive information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Because of the nature of our services, some information we handle may be sensitive or deeply personal in context, even where it is not formally classified as sensitive information by law.\
\
We do not seek to collect sensitive information unless it is reasonably necessary for our business functions or services, permitted by law, or provided with consent.\
\
For example, sensitive or delicate information may arise where:\
\
a. you provide religious, cultural, ceremonial, or memorial preferences;\
\
b. you provide authority documents connected with a death, estate, or family arrangements;\
\
c. you provide special instructions relating to grief, emotional circumstances, or memorial content.\
\
Where you provide information to us about another person, you must ensure you are authorised to do so.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 6. How we collect personal information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may collect personal information directly from you when you:\
\
a. contact us through the website, email, phone, or social channels;\
\
b. request a quote;\
\
c. complete a booking form or enquiry form;\
\
d. provide delivery or memorial instructions;\
\
e. make payment;\
\
f. send documentation or declarations;\
\
g. subscribe to updates;\
\
h. communicate with us about a Booking or service issue.\
\
We may also collect personal information from third parties where reasonably necessary, including:\
\
a. funeral homes;\
\
b. crematoriums;\
\
c. veterinary clinics or pet cremation providers;\
\
d. authorised family members or representatives;\
\
e. couriers and logistics providers;\
\
f. payment providers;\
\
g. IT, website, CRM, and communications providers;\
\
h. publicly available sources, where relevant to verifying contact or authority information.\
\
If we receive personal information from a third party, we may assume that the third party has the right to provide that information to us unless we have reason to believe otherwise.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 7. Why we collect personal information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We collect personal information for purposes including:\
\
a. responding to enquiries and providing quotes;\
\
b. assessing and accepting Bookings;\
\
c. confirming identity, authority, and service instructions;\
\
d. arranging intake, transport coordination, delivery handling, and scheduling;\
\
e. providing the Service and any additional deliverables;\
\
f. generating certificates, memorial records, and media files;\
\
g. processing payments and administering accounts;\
\
h. communicating with Clients and authorised recipients;\
\
i. maintaining internal business records;\
\
j. handling complaints, incidents, disputes, chargebacks, or legal claims;\
\
k. protecting our legal rights and interests;\
\
l. improving our website, systems, and services;\
\
m. complying with legal, regulatory, insurance, and audit requirements;\
\
n. conducting internal training, quality assurance, and operational review;\
\
o. sending updates, service notices, or marketing communications where permitted by law.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 8. What happens if you do not provide information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
If you do not provide information we reasonably require, we may be unable to:\
\
a. respond to your enquiry properly;\
\
b. confirm a Booking;\
\
c. verify authority or identity;\
\
d. accept delivery of Cremated Remains;\
\
e. provide the Service;\
\
f. provide a certificate, video, memorial record, or other deliverable;\
\
g. comply with legal or safety obligations.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 9. How we use personal information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may use personal information:\
\
a. to identify and communicate with you;\
\
b. to manage enquiries, quotes, and Bookings;\
\
c. to verify authority and instructions;\
\
d. to coordinate service delivery and operational logistics;\
\
e. to issue invoices, process payments, and manage financial records;\
\
f. to prepare certificates, memorial records, and service deliverables;\
\
g. to provide customer support;\
\
h. to improve and maintain our website and systems;\
\
i. to enforce our Terms and Conditions and other policies;\
\
j. to investigate errors, fraud, misuse, packaging failures, disputes, or complaints;\
\
k. to protect our staff, contractors, customers, and business operations;\
\
l. to meet legal obligations.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 10. Direct marketing
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may use your personal information to send you communications about our services, updates, or related offerings where permitted by law.\
\
These communications may be sent by email, SMS, telephone, or other electronic means.\
\
You may opt out of marketing communications at any time by:\
\
a. using the unsubscribe facility in the message, if available;\
\
b. contacting us using the details in this Privacy Policy.\
\
Even if you opt out of marketing communications, we may still send you non-promotional communications necessary to administer a Booking, provide a Service, or comply with law.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 11. Cookies and website tracking
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to:\
\
a. enable website functionality;\
\
b. remember user preferences;\
\
c. analyse site traffic and performance;\
\
d. improve user experience;\
\
e. support security and fraud prevention;\
\
f. support advertising or remarketing functions if implemented.\
\
You may be able to disable cookies through your browser settings, but doing so may affect website functionality.\
\
Where required by law or best practice, we may implement cookie notices, cookie controls, or consent tools.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 12. When we disclose personal information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may disclose personal information where reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, including to:\
\
a. our employees, contractors, and authorised representatives;\
\
b. payment processors and financial service providers;\
\
c. website hosting, software, CRM, email, and IT service providers;\
\
d. couriers, postal operators, and logistics providers;\
\
e. aviation, operational, and service contractors;\
\
f. funeral homes, cremation providers, veterinary or pet cremation providers, or other service partners involved in a Booking;\
\
g. professional advisers including lawyers, accountants, insurers, auditors, and consultants;\
\
h. regulators, law enforcement agencies, courts, tribunals, or government bodies where required or authorised by law;\
\
i. other persons or entities where you have expressly authorised the disclosure.\
\
We do not sell personal information as a standalone product.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 13. Disclosure to authorised recipients and family contacts
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Because our services are often arranged on behalf of families, estates, or other interested persons, we may disclose service-related information, media, memorial records, or status updates to persons we reasonably believe are authorised recipients or authorised contacts for the Booking.\
\
We may require evidence of authority before making disclosures, particularly where the disclosure is sensitive, contested, or potentially intrusive.\
\
If there is a dispute regarding authority, we may refuse to disclose information until the dispute is resolved to our reasonable satisfaction.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 14. Overseas disclosure
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Some of our technology, cloud storage, email, payment, analytics, or software providers may store or process information outside Australia.\
\
By dealing with us, you acknowledge that personal information may be transferred to, stored in, or accessed from countries outside Australia where this is reasonably necessary for our business operations.\
\
We take reasonable steps to ensure service providers handle information appropriately, but overseas jurisdictions may have different privacy laws from Australia.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 15. Storage and security
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We take reasonable steps to protect personal information from misuse, interference, loss, unauthorised access, unauthorised modification, and unauthorised disclosure.\
\
Measures we may use include:\
\
a. secure software systems and account controls;\
\
b. password protection and role-based access;\
\
c. secure cloud platforms or restricted internal storage;\
\
d. staff confidentiality measures;\
\
e. secure disposal procedures;\
\
f. limited-access handling of service records and memorial files.\
\
No method of transmission over the internet and no method of electronic storage is completely secure. While we take reasonable precautions, we cannot guarantee absolute security.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 16. How long we keep information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We keep personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, and for any longer period required or permitted by law, insurance requirements, dispute resolution needs, taxation obligations, or business record-keeping requirements.\
\
The period we keep information may depend on:\
\
a. the nature of the Booking;\
\
b. whether the Service was completed;\
\
c. whether a complaint, dispute, or legal issue has arisen;\
\
d. whether the information forms part of a memorial record or service record;\
\
e. our legal and operational obligations.\
\
When information is no longer required, we may delete it, de-identify it, archive it securely, or destroy it.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 17. Access to and correction of personal information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
You may request access to personal information we hold about you, and you may request correction of personal information that is inaccurate, out of date, incomplete, irrelevant, or misleading.\
\
We may ask you to verify your identity before giving access or making a correction.\
\
We may refuse access or correction where permitted by law, including where:\
\
a. granting access would unreasonably affect the privacy of another person;\
\
b. the request is frivolous or vexatious;\
\
c. legal privilege applies;\
\
d. the information relates to an anticipated or existing dispute or proceeding;\
\
e. we are otherwise lawfully permitted or required to refuse.\
\
If we refuse access or correction, we will generally provide written reasons unless it would be unreasonable to do so.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 18. Dealing with information about other people
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
If you provide us with personal information about another person, you warrant that:\
\
a. you are authorised to provide that information;\
\
b. the person has been informed, where appropriate, that their information may be provided to us and handled in accordance with this Privacy Policy; and\
\
c. any instructions or consents you provide on their behalf are valid.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 19. Children\'92s information
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Our services are not directed to children. We do not knowingly collect personal information directly from children except where it is reasonably incidental to a Booking, memorial record, or family-related communication and is lawfully provided by a parent, guardian, or authorised adult.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 20. Anonymity and pseudonymity
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Where lawful and practicable, you may deal with us anonymously or by pseudonym, such as when making a general enquiry.\
\
However, for most Bookings and service-related matters, this will not be practical because we need to verify identity, authority, contact details, payment, and service instructions.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 21. Complaints about privacy
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
If you believe we have mishandled your personal information or breached applicable privacy law, you may make a complaint by contacting us using the details below.\
\
Your complaint should include enough detail for us to understand the issue and investigate it.\
\
We will review the complaint and respond within a reasonable time.\
\
If you are dissatisfied with our response, you may have the right to escalate the matter to the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner or another relevant authority.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 22. Third-party websites and services
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Our website or communications may contain links to third-party websites, platforms, or services.\
\
We are not responsible for the privacy practices, security, or content of third-party websites or services. You should review their privacy policies separately.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 23. Changes to this Privacy Policy
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.\
\
The updated version will be published on our website with the revised effective date or last updated date.\
\
Your continued dealings with us after an updated Privacy Policy is published constitute acknowledgment of the updated policy, to the extent permitted by law.\
\

